AIM: 
To write a C program to store and display details of multiple students using array of structures. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Define a structure Student with members: 
 ->name (string) 
 ->roll (integer) 
 -> marks (float) 
3. Declare an array of Student structure, e.g., struct Student s[SIZE]. 
4. Read the number of students n. 
5. For each student i from 0 to n-1: 
 -> Accept name, roll, and marks. 
6. Display the details of all students using a loop. 
7. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
struct Student { 
char name[20]; 
int roll; 
float marks; 
}; 
int main() { 
struct Student s[100]; // Array of structures 
int n, i; 
printf("Enter number of students: "); 
scanf("%d", &n); 
// Input student details 
for(i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
printf("\nEnter details for student %d:\n", i+1); 
printf("Name: "); 
scanf("%s", s[i].name); 
printf("Roll Number: "); 
scanf("%d", &s[i].roll); 
printf("Marks: "); 
scanf("%f", &s[i].marks); 
} 
// Display student details 
printf("\nStudent Details:\n"); 
printf(" \n"); 
printf("Name\tRoll\tMarks\n"); 
printf(" \n"); 
for(i = 0; i < n; i++) { 
printf("%s\t%d\t%.2f\n", s[i].name, s[i].roll, s[i].marks); 
} 
return 0; 
} 
 
 
